		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Need advice<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Apr 23rd 1:20 PM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=10511161362001&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=10511161362001&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=10511161362001"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10511161362001></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=152352"><span id=Scholar>OssO</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>34 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=OssO&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hello all :).<br>I wanna make a char on a PvP server (this would be my first time) and i can't decide between a shadow knight or a necro. I would like to know which one has more chances to survive, which one makes better duels or which one is more fun :P.<br>I have heard that people gets more fun on pvp servers so idecided to try it. (i have this post in Necro section too) Thanks for info in advance :).<br><br>Ozzer DE Rogue lvl 60 on AB server</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Apr 23rd 2:25 PM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=10511161362001&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=10511200182294"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10511200182294></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=145263"><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>389 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=lunaticfringesk&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>There was actually a recent discussion re: SHD vs NEC on the SHD boards.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some SHDs are claiming that, all things equal, if the NEC has &quot;1/2 a brain&quot; the SHD has no chance.<br><br>I am very skeptical of this sentiment.  HT is rather powerful in PvP, to say nothing about what UT3 does.<br><br>If I understand correctly, the idea is that they have a better pet, more mana efficient lifetaps, and basically do a strategy similar to what I have seen a BST do---run around and let your pet do damage while you chase the NEC/BST.  They will get their MR up high enough, or so they claim, that landing snare is very difficult/impossible.<br><br>I guess Im going to have to get some NEC guildees and play around a little, because I just dont get it.<br><br>If they are running around, they sure as heck arent casting any spells.  They stop to cast and you are running towards them, it wont take long b4 you are in melee range and put the hurting on them.  I think most people will operate under the presumtion that they will take a few hits to get a spell to land.  A NEC, however, has a terrible defense and a few swipes from a SHD weapon will make him think about it Im sure.<br><br>And relying on SS to bail you out isnt exactly guaranteed either.  SS can be horribly unreliable.  I have cast that thing 3 straight times, with 2 of them barely even moving me and me having to wait to the 3rd cast to get away (when you are getting worked by a warrior, ranger and chanter, best to get out of there!!).<br><br>And it stands to reason that if they could increase their MR high enough to make a lot of spells land, the SHD could do the same.  Granted, a NEC can do dmg across damn near all resists, but it isnt too hard to increase them all at the same time.<br><br>I still believe, at the moment, that a SHD is one of the best PvP classes out there.  A NEC, however, can also be a fierce opponent, so you probably cant go wrong picking either.  I will say, however, that a SHD probably has a little less risk involved in dueling though.  They can take a healthy beating--a NEC cannot.<br><br>Luna</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
